ng and Buffing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Be patient. Ideally everyone should know the location of the meeting place and be there waiting. However, this is not always the case. Arranging ports for people takes time and requires the patients of all involved.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Don’t mess around. When you get to the designated area sit and pay attention. You don’t want to miss the invite into the group that you are positioned in.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp After grouping but before moving into the buffing area there will be a 2 minute downtime to go afk for a pop/beer run, bio, and quick smoke.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp There may be multiple channels set up. Listen to the raid leader and /join (channel or channels) that you are told to join.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  DO NOT spam these channels with useless chatting. The raid and group leaders will be using these channels to give orders and special instructions. Use guild chat for all unnecessary chat.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp DO NOT spam the RL (raid leader) or GL’s (group leaders) as they are sending/receiving instructions as well as the ones they need to give to you.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The group leaders are responsible for the buffs for their group. This means that they will ask the buffer in raid channel to buff their group. As well as inform a buffer in their group to buff another group.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Do not ask for unnecessary buffs.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp All questions should be ask to your group leader who will then answer or send a tell to the raid leader. The raid leader has too much going on to try to keep track of a hundred different tells.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Do as you are told as quickly as possible. This will ensure a speedy grouping and buffing session. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp If you are unsure about anything this is the time to ask. No one thinks badly of a person that doesn’t understand something. With all the different buffs its sometimes hard to remember which buffs stack and which ones don’t.<br>
